The resolution header confirms that this is happening within "tỉnh Hưng Yên", which aligns with the province merger I identified earlier.  Now, to be absolutely sure, I'll quickly reference the `New wards` list... and there it is: `{"ward_code":"12700","ward_name":"Xã Bắc Tiên Hưng","province_name":"Tỉnh Hưng Yên"}`.  Spot on.

So, here's my confident conclusion: the new administrative unit for "Xã Lô Giang, Huyện Đông Hưng, Tỉnh Thái Bình" is **"Xã Bắc Tiên Hưng" in "Tỉnh Hưng Yên"**. I'm very confident because I've found a direct match and a clear resolution that outlines the change. I'll make sure to cite that resolution in the output!
